President Trump held a press conference in the Oval Office where he discussed the need for border security and signed legislation to combat human trafficking. He expressed concern about the dangerous situation at the border and emphasized the importance of a strong barrier to prevent illegal immigration and trafficking. The President also mentioned the need for comprehensive immigration reform and expressed his willingness to declare a national emergency if a deal cannot be reached with Congress. He acknowledged the impact of the government shutdown on federal workers but stated that border security is a priority. The President highlighted the support he has received from Republicans and expressed his hope for a bipartisan solution.